From fd6a5db2d19800184175c29707fef2d74b544603 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 17:48:51 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 9/9] [DOSKUTSU] SDL3_image: drop IMG_Init / IMG_INIT_PNG /
 IMG_GetError block
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Why DOS needs this: SDL3_image (`build/sysroot/include/SDL3_image/SDL_image.h`)
removed `IMG_Init`, `IMG_Quit`, the `IMG_INIT_*` flag enum, and `IMG_GetError`
entirely. Decoders are initialised lazily on first `IMG_Load`. The check that
NXEngine's main.cpp performs at lines 312-318 ("init PNG decoder, abort if it
fails") has no equivalent in the SDL3_image API — PNG support is a build-time
feature (we built with stb_image enabled in #28, so it's always available).

Site: src/main.cpp lines 312-318 — the entire IMG_Init block removed.
Comment-block placeholder retained to document why nothing replaces it.

NOT touched in this patch:
- `IMG_Load` (Renderer.cpp:140, Font.cpp:74) — signature is identical in
  SDL3_image (`SDL_Surface *IMG_Load(const char *file)`); no change needed.
- `#include <SDL_image.h>` — kept; the SDL3_image install puts the header
  at `<SDL3_image/SDL_image.h>` but the build's CMake config will add
  `-I .../include/SDL3_image`, so the bare include resolves correctly. If
  that turns out wrong at build time it's an include-path fix in the
  CMakeLists port patch (#33), not here.

Per #27 audit, total IMG_* surface in NXEngine was: IMG_Load (×2), IMG_Init,
IMG_INIT_PNG, IMG_GetError. Three of those go away (IMG_Init/INIT_PNG/GetError),
two survive unchanged (IMG_Load). This is the entire delta.

Companion to 0010-0012 SDL3 migration patches and the upcoming 0013-0017
audio refactor. No interaction with the audio cluster — this is pure
image-loader API drift.
---
 src/main.cpp | 10 ++++------
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/main.cpp b/src/main.cpp
index 86e95a7..ef005fd 100644
--- a/src/main.cpp
+++ b/src/main.cpp
@@ -310,12 +310,10 @@ int main(int argc, char *argv[])
     return 1;
   }
 
-  int flags = IMG_INIT_PNG;
-  int initted = IMG_Init(flags);
-  if((initted & flags) != flags) {
-    LOG_CRITICAL("IMG_Init: Failed to init required png support: {}", IMG_GetError());
-    return 1;
-  }
+  // SDL3_image: IMG_Init / IMG_Quit / IMG_INIT_* / IMG_GetError are gone.
+  // Decoders are initialised lazily on first IMG_Load — no explicit init
+  // step is needed. PNG support is built into SDL3_image at compile time
+  // (we built with stb_image enabled), so it's available without a flag.
 
   // start up inputs first thing because settings_load may remap them
   input_init();
-- 
